    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8231" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥήγνῡμι</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝρ.</span>, cf. frango), 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥηγνῦσι</span>, ipf. iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥήγνυσκε</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥήξω</span>, aor.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔρρηξα, ῥῆξε</span>, mid. pres. imp.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥήγνυσθε</span>, aor. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐρ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ρήξαντο</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">break, burst, rend</span> in twain, different from <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄγνῡμι</span>. Freq. of breaking the ranks of the
          enemy in battle, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φάλαγγας, ὅμῑλον,
            στίχας,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 6.6</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Λ
            538</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.615</span></i>.—Mid.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">break</span> for oneself, <i><span class="en">Il.
            11.90</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 12.90</span></i>;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">break</span> intrans., as waves, and fig., ‘let break out,’
          ‘let loose,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔριδα</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 20.55</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
